	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f99964607569453>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>Earth pet issue</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, Sep 4th 7:27 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Ive recently hit level 12 and invested again in the Earth pet.&nbsp;&nbsp;It just doesn't seem to be as capable in bringing down Mobs as the Water and Fire.  Fighting for me is pretty standard.  Fire Shield pet, Shock of Blades, Pet attack, Shock till its just about dead, let pet finish.  When I use an earth pet he seems to cast root every couple of hits.  Then the rooted mob hits on my pet till it dies.  With a water pet the targets drop faster and my pet seems to last longer.  I haven't had a single target ignore my pets attack and come after me when I backed away, and the Pets root drops when the pet dies.  So where's the benefit?<br>Is it not an issue untill later levels?  If so when?<br><br>******Amayarick, Saryrn server.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	     <tr><td colspan=2 align=right class=mform id=fs8>2 Replies</td></tr>
